TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bordalo, Pedro
AU  - Gennaioli, Nicola
AU  - Shleifer, Andrei
T1  - Salience Theory of Choice Under Risk
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjs018
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 127
IS  - 3
SP  - 1243
EP  - 1285
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  -  We present a theory of choice among lotteries in which the decision maker's attention is drawn to (precisely defined) salient payoffs. This leads the decision maker to a context-dependent representation of lotteries in which true probabilities are replaced by decision weights distorted in favor of salient payoffs. By specifying decision weights as a function of payoffs, our model provides a novel and unified account of many empirical phenomena, including frequent risk-seeking behavior, invariance failures such as the Allais paradox, and preference reversals. It also yields new predictions, including some that distinguish it from prospect theory, which we test. 
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjs018
ER  - 



